content.description: Starts on a big sit start ledge. Huge move to a perfect incut slot. Mantle the ledge while going to another good hold a bit higher. Stand on the ledge and top out. Tall Boulder but super easy top out
content.location: Get to the “A Wrinkle In Time” Boulder, cut into the woods past it, and it will be in the woods about 100 feet from the trail.

content.description: A high quality lowball with unique moves for the area. Start with a high standing reach to a blind crack. Left hand starts in a small mono indentation. Slap hard to the sloper and shuffle feet up, move towards the right and top out. Potential for much harder problems further down the cliff band.
content.location: Directly on the trail. As you walk to the second overlook, it will be on your right.

content.description: This area is between the first and second lookouts. About a 20 minute hike, passing the first overlook and continuing for another 4-5 minutes. A few large glacial erratics and small cliff outcrops define the zone. Very high rock quality and very clean rock in this area. Lots of slabs and slopers. Landings are generally less than perfect in this area.
